The Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU), community on Saturday was thrown into mourning mood following the death of a final year student, Opeyemi Dara.
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1208461 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?resize=600%2C371&#038;ssl=1" alt="STUDENT " width="600" height="371" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?resize=300%2C186&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?resize=58%2C36&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?resize=260%2C161&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?resize=200%2C124&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?resize=160%2C100&amp;ssl=1 160w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Hang-rope.jpg?resize=560%2C346&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The deceased was said to be a student of Faculty of Arts, Department of English Language, who allegedly committed suicide after taking a suspected dose of lethal substance popularly known as “snipper”. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) learnt that she allegedly took her life following her poor academic performance, although the details of the incident were still sketchy. The authorities of the institution confirmed that the deceased committed suicide following depression occasioned by poor academic records. Dara’s academic records obtained indicated that she had five outstanding courses and 12 Special Electives. When contacted, the Public Relations Officer of OAU, Mr Abiodun Olanrewaju confirmed the incident and promised that the institution would investigate and make its findings public. Olarewaju appealed to students not to contemplate committing suicide because of poor academic performance, We can end Nigerians’ craze for varsity education abroad – Aluyor, Edo University VC(Opens in a new browser tab) “ We sympathise with the parents and guardian of the deceased known as Dara. ” We just want our students and young ones to know that depression is not a thing they should encourage, no matter the situation or circumstance they find themselves. “ Some people in the past have passed through the same situation and circumstances and came out clean. “Now, suicide can never be an option and people, especially the young ones who believe that taking their own lives is an act of gallantry should know that it is not . “We want to appeal to students, particularly OAU students to take things easy. Any child that fails; that is why the university says you can rerun a course, you can resit a course. “People out there also face challenges and when you are in school, failure or repetition of a course or particular subject is also part of the challenges students must face. “The university will get to the root of the incident and get back to the public,” Olarewaju said. VANGUARD